 nodes. Unsplittability means that when\na negligible fraction of sensors are captured, almost all of the remaining\nnodes are still securely connected. Based on the results of connectivity,\nunassailability and unsplittability, we provide useful guidelines for the\ndesign of secure sensor networks.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 2 Nov 2019 14:52:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-05"}
